# Capture Repeated Preferences

When the user gives the same instruction or correction **more than once** (a
recurring styling/behaviour/convention preference):

1. Briefly confirm the intended convention with the user (ask, don't assume the
   exact scope/values).
2. Once confirmed, write it into `.cursor/rules/` as a focused, always-apply rule
   with a concrete BAD/GOOD example.
3. Apply it consistently across the codebase from then on, so the topic doesn't
   need to be discussed again.

The goal is a cohesive system: preferences become durable rules instead of being
re-litigated each session.
